### ============================================================
### IncidentController - API Tests
### SC_043 - M7-US-03b (incident-detail-unlocked)
### SC_044 - M7-US-03  (incident-detail-nurse)
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents
### ============================================================

# ── SC_044: GET incident detail (Nurse/CNA read-only view) ───────────────────

### [1] GET incident detail - as NURSE
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
X-User-Role: NURSE

###

### [2] GET incident detail - as CNA
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
X-User-Role: CNA

###

### [3] GET incident detail - as DON
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
X-User-Role: DON

###

### [4] GET incident detail - as ADMIN
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
X-User-Role: ADMIN

###

### [5] GET incident detail - incident not found (404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/9999
X-User-Role: NURSE

###

### [6] GET incident detail - UNAUTHORIZED (no role header)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1

###

# ── SC_043: PUT unlock incident (DON only) ───────────────────────────────────

### [7] PUT unlock incident - DON with reason and password
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: DON

{
  "reason": "Problem resolved. Resident condition stable. No further investigation needed.",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

###

### [8] PUT unlock incident - as ADMIN
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/2
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: ADMIN

{
  "reason": "Incident reviewed and closed by admin.",
  "password": "adminPass456"
}

###

### [9] PUT unlock incident - missing reason (400)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: DON

{
  "reason": "",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

###

### [10] PUT unlock incident - incident not found (404)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/9999
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: DON

{
  "reason": "Resolved",
  "password": "pass"
}

###

### [11] PUT unlock incident - FORBIDDEN (NURSE cannot unlock)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: NURSE

{
  "reason": "Trying to unlock",
  "password": "pass"
}

###

### [12] PUT unlock incident - FORBIDDEN (CNA cannot unlock)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: CNA

{
  "reason": "Trying to unlock",
  "password": "pass"
}

###

### [13] PUT unlock incident - UNAUTHORIZED (no role header)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Resolved",
  "password": "pass"
}

###

# ── SC_043: POST add timeline entry ─────────────────────────────────────────

### [14] POST add timeline - NURSE adds update
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1/timelines
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: NURSE

{
  "action": "Physician notified. Resident vitals monitored every 2 hours.",
  "reason": null
}

###

### [15] POST add timeline - CNA adds note
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1/timelines
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: CNA

{
  "action": "Resident assisted back to bed. No visible injuries.",
  "reason": null
}

###

### [16] POST add timeline - DON adds investigation note
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1/timelines
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: DON

{
  "action": "Investigation initiated. Family notified.",
  "reason": "Significant incident requiring DON review"
}

###

### [17] POST add timeline - missing action (400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1/timelines
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: NURSE

{
  "action": "",
  "reason": null
}

###

### [18] POST add timeline - incident not found (404)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/9999/timelines
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: NURSE

{
  "action": "Test action",
  "reason": null
}

###

### [19] POST add timeline - UNAUTHORIZED (no role header)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/incidents/1/timelines
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "Test",
  "reason": null
}

